Shaftesbury Says First-Half Pretax Profit Declined to About $163 Million

-- B y   A n d r e w   B l a c k m a n
-- 
2011-05-25T06:03:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/shaftesbury-says-first-half-pretax-profit-declined-to-about-163-million.html
Shaftesbury Plc (SHB) , the owner of more
than 500 shops, restaurants and office buildings in central
 London , said its first-half pretax profit fell to 101 million
pounds from 122.8 million pounds a year earlier, according to a
statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at 
 ablackman@bloomberg.net  